relation: Microsatellite allele sizes are always presented as "smaller,larger" so that a 5 digit entry can be decoded as smaller=first 2 digits, larger=last 3 digits. A "0" or blank means data are missing. A 3-digit entry refers to a homozygote. For sex, a "1" refers to male while a "0" refers to female.
